weatherspect
-------------------------------------------
WeatherSpect provides a reasonably accurate simulation of what the 
weather looks like outside, in ASCII art. It includes rain, snow, 
lightning, sleet, and hail.

Runtime requirements:
  perl-5.8.8-4
  perl-Curses-1.17-1
  perl-Term-Animation-2.4-1
  perl-Weather-Underground-3.02-1

Canonical homepage:
  http://robobunny.com/projects/weatherspect/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack weatherspect-1.8-1-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./weatherspect-1.8-1.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/weatherspect-1.8-1-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/weatherspect-1.8-1.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/bin/weatherspect
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/weatherspect-1.8.README
  /usr/share/doc/weatherspect-1.8/CHANGES
  /usr/share/doc/weatherspect-1.8/GPL.txt
  /usr/share/doc/weatherspect-1.8/README

------------------

Port Notes:

----- version 1.8-1 -----
Version bump, requires Term::Animation 2.4.

----- version 1.6-1 -----
New upstream release for Weather::Underground 3.0.

----- version 1.5-1 -----
New upstream release for Term::Animation 2.0.

----- version 1.4-1 -----
New upstream release; fixes bugs with cloud rendering.

----- version 1.2-1 -----
New upstream release.

  - Fix for new temperature and wind formats

----- version 1.1-1 -----
Initial release for Cygwin.


